'''Morgan Lee Lander''' (born [[January 6]], [[1982]]) is the lead singer and guitarist for the [[Canada|Canadian]] [[alternative metal]] group [[Kittie]]. Her sister, [[Mercedes Lander]], also plays for Kittie.
==Biography==
===Early life=== 
Morgan Lee Lander was born to Dave and Deanna Lander in [[Edmonton, Alberta, Canada]] on [[January 6]], [[1982]]. Two years later, Morgan became the big sister of [[Mercedes Lander]], the drummer and founding members of [[Kittie]].

At the age of two, she moved to [[London, Ontario]], where she still lives to this day. When Morgan was six, she started to take piano lessons, but soon grew tired and started to play guitar for a couple of years. She started to compose her first songs when she was 13 (including Kittie's breakthrough hit, [[Brackish (song)|Brackish]]) with Mercedes and friend, [[Fallon Bowman]].

===Kittie debut (1996)===
In [[1996]], when Morgan was 14, Merecedes, Fallon, and [[Tanya Candler]] formed [[Kittie]]. Three years later, the band released their breakthrough first album, [[Spit (album)|Spit]].

===Poisoned Black Clothing (2005)===
Morgan is also a successful business woman, she currently co-owns a clothing line called Poisoned Black Clothing with her younger sister, Mercedes. Poisoned Black Clothing officially launched in September 2005, and aims to provide an alternative style for 'cute boys and hot girls'. Morgan also co-owns a management with her family called Kiss Of Infamy, later changed to X of Infamy. She currently manages two up-and-coming bands.

==Personal Life==
Morgan is currently engaged to Justin Wolfe of [[Canada|Canadian]] band [[Thine Eyes Bleed]].

==Influences==
All her life Morgan has been interested and somehow involved in music. As a child she and her younger sister Mercedes would dress up and pretend to be in a band called the 'Beautiful Bitches'. Her favourite bands include: [[Far (band)|Far]], [[Silverchair]], [[The Gathering (band)|The Gathering]], [[Code Seven]], [[A Perfect Circle|APC]], [[Rammstein]], [[Pantera]], [[Metallica]], [[Cephalic Carnage]], [[Neurosis (band)|Neurosis]], [[Today is the Day]], [[Acid Bath]], [[The Haunted]], [[Lamb of God (band)|Lamb of God]], [[Cave In]], [[Acacia]], [[The Icarus Line]], [[Slayer]], [[Jonah Matranga]], [[The Weakerthans]], [[Chamberlain (band)|Chamberlain]], [[Opeth]], [[New End Original]], [[Mastodon (band)|Mastodon]], [[December (band)|December]], [[HIM (band)|HIM]], [[Farside (band)|Farside]], [[Adina Howard]], [[SWV]], [[Thine Eyes Bleed]], [[TLC (band)|TLC]], [[Rick James]] and [[Slipknot (band)|Slipknot]].

